.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-REACHABILITY" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-reachability \- check if a remote node is reachable
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-reachability
.I peer_id
.SH DESCRIPTION
Attempts to find a route to the target node using
.B getroute
with a 1000 msat probe amount.
Returns whether a route exists and its estimated fee.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"peer_id":"...","reachable":bool,
 "route_hops":N,"fee_estimate_msat":N}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-route-find (1),
.BR lightning-peer-info (1)
